        "content": "<p>You can use <code>cases</code> on <code>n : ℤ</code> to split it into cases <code>ofNat n</code> and <code>negSucc n</code> for <code>n : ℕ</code>. But is there some other way I can split it into cases <code>↑n</code> and <code>-↑n</code> for <code>n : ℕ</code>? This would be slightly nicer in my application.</p>",
        "id": 506289532,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1742256836
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can't make this a recursor without deciding what to do at 0, but as an induction principle seems fine</p>",
